Translation: Ahmad b. Muhammad al-Nuri de Bagdad, Moradas de los corazones [Maqama al-qulub] (Madrid 1999); i.e., Stations of the Heart, said to have been an [indirect] source of the mystical symbolism of seven concentric castles employed by St. Teresa of Avila; also see L&lt;U+00F3&gt;pez-Baralt, Islam in Spanish Literature (1985, 1992) at 107-115, esp. 110.
Editors (with Eulogio Pacho): San Juan de la Cruz, Obra completa (Madrid: Alianza 1994), 2 volumes.

